article.headline: N. Carolina A&amp,T 75, Winston-Salem 56
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Steven Rush scored 23 points to lead North Carolina A&T past Winston-Salem State 75-56 on Saturday in the teams' first meeting in 10 seasons. Jason Wills and Austin Ewing added 12 points apiece for the Aggies (9-9), who shot nearly 47 percent in the decisive first half and built a 19-point halftime lead. Jamal Durham had 17 points and 10 rebounds for the Rams (8-10), who are in their second season at the Division I level and are playing a full Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference schedule, even though they are not yet eligible to win the league title. North Carolina A&T outrebounded the Rams 48-43 and held them to just 13.6 percent shooting from 3-point range.
